obo:UBERON_0002421  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_2157  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Background: paper shows that stargazin regulates AMPAR trafficking via differential interactions with AP-2 and AP-3 depending on the phosphorylation state of stargazin. The interaction of stargazin with both AP-3 and AP-2 seems to be needed for NMDA-induced AMPA receptor endocytosis, a chemical LTD model, in hippocampal neurons. This is unexpected since only AP-2 complex is known to be involved in clathrin-mediated endocytosis. In further experiments the authors show that it is not the endocytosis that is regulated by AP-3, but the targeting to the lysosomal compartment; if AP-3 function is perturbed the AMPARs are no longer degraded, but travel back to the plasma membrane preventing a run-down of the cell surface receptor levels.\n\nFig 5-S5: \"Knockdown of AP-2 or AP-3A inhibits the NMDA-induced removal of surface AMPA receptors\"\n\nFig.7: \"Suppression of hippocampal CA1-LTD by inhibiting the interaction of STG with AP-2 or AP-3A\"\nThis figure supports the relevance of the AP-2 role in in vivo synapses (AP-2 function is perturbed indirectly).\n\nNote: authors knocked down two members of the AP-2 complex, beta2 and mu: \"The function of AP-2β can be partly compensated by a highly similar subunit, AP-1β (ref. 23), which is normally incorporated into AP-1. Therefore, to further clarify the specific roles had by AP-2, we knocked down AP-2μ.\" This makes an argument to annotate other members of the AP-2 complex to the same term.\n\nNote: the paper mentions shRNA against AP-2 β2 subunit. This subunit does not exist in Unitprot. This is traced back to subunit β2 adaptin (PMID:17290217) which is an alternative name for AP-2 beta1: \"PIP5Kγ661 interacts with the AP-2 complex subunit β2 adaptin\". Experimental description: \"Hippocampi dissected from E16-E17 ICR mice were treated with 10 U ml-1 trypsin and 100 U....\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7806-5662" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2157" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

